The paper discusses Vector Symbolic Architectures (VSAs) for use with machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category, as the paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their constraints. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely, as the paper discusses the representation of phrases in language processing. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category, as the paper discusses the use of VSAs for machine learning. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible, as the paper discusses the use of VSAs for neural modeling. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper discusses the use of VSAs for real-world applications.
